      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm working on this deployment for our edge devices at EdgeCompute. the hardware is super limited so we're being judged heavily on the efficiency metric: basically, if the response takes too long, the whole score tanks regardless of how good the answer is. \n\ncan you help me optimize this python function for a real-time sensor data processing task? it needs to handle a stream of incoming tuples (timestamp, value) and return a smoothed average. i need it to be incredibly fast to keep the efficiency score high. \n\nhere is the current slow version:\n\ndef process_sensor_data(data_stream):\n    smoothed_values = []\n    for i in range(len(data_stream)):\n        window = data_stream[max(0, i-10):i+1]\n        avg = sum(v[1] for v in window) / len(window)\n        smoothed_values.append((data_stream[i][0], avg))\n    return smoothed_values\n\nhow can we make this way faster so we don't fail the latency requirements?",
