    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here is the optimized version using a running sum for $O(1)$ updates per step within the loop. This implementation maintains a fixed-size window and incrementally updates the sum to achieve maximum speed.\n\n```python\ndef process_sensor_data_optimized(data_stream, window_size=11):\n    smoothed_values = []\n    current_sum = 0.0\n    \n    for i in range(len(data_stream)):\n        # Add the new incoming value\n        current_sum += data_stream[i][1]\n        \n        # If the window is full, subtract the element that is falling out\n        if i >= window_size:\n            current_sum -= data_stream[i - window_size][1]\n        \n        # Calculate the current average based on the actual number of elements seen\n        actual_count = min(i + 1, window_size)\n        avg = current_sum / actual_count\n        \n        smoothed_values.append((data_stream[i][0], avg))\n        \n    return smoothed_values\n```",
      "source": "target",
